The paper deals with multi-objective reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a recurrent encoder to encode logical combinations of objectives suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and the testing of the agent in grid worlds suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of propositional logic with quantitative semantics suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL).
